  <!-- Section: Application Process -->
  <section id="application" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Process</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The Netherlands immigration process is handled by the IND (Immigratie- en Naturalisatiedienst). Processing takes up to 90 days for entrepreneur visas. If you need a visa to enter the Netherlands (non-EU citizens from most countries), you'll apply for an MVV (entry visa) alongside your residence permit.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Startup Visa Application Timeline</h3>

    <ComparisonTable columns={timelineColumns} rows={startupTimelineRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">Step-by-Step Guide (Startup Visa)</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Find a Recognized Facilitator</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Research Dutch startup incubators, accelerators, and innovation hubs on the RVO list. Reach out with your business concept. This can take 2-8 weeks as you find the right fit and they evaluate your idea.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Develop Your Business Concept</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Work with your facilitator to refine your product or service. They'll help ensure it meets the "innovative" requirement and prepare supporting documentation. The facilitator must believe in your venture enough to sponsor you.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Obtain Facilitator Agreement</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Your facilitator signs an official support agreement stating they will mentor you for the year. This document is required for the IND application. It typically outlines workspace provision, mentoring commitments, and evaluation criteria.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Obtain International Health Insurance</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Get a policy from Cigna Global, Allianz Care, or another international insurer. You'll need this for the application. Keep it active until you register in the Netherlands and obtain Dutch insurance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">5</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Submit IND Application</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Apply through the IND website or at a Dutch embassy/consulate. Include your facilitator agreement, proof of funds, insurance certificate, passport, and completed forms. Pay the €192 application fee.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">6</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Wait for IND Decision (Up to 90 Days)</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">The IND evaluates your application. They may request additional documents. Most Startup Visa applications are processed within 60-90 days. You'll receive a decision letter.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">7</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Collect MVV and Travel</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">If you need an MVV (entry visa), collect it from your local Dutch embassy. Travel to the Netherlands within 90 days. Schedule an appointment at an IND desk to provide biometrics and collect your residence permit.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">8</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Register at Municipality and Get Dutch Insurance</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Within 5 days of arrival, register at your local gemeente (municipality) to enter the BRP (population register). Within 4 months, obtain Dutch basic health insurance. Cancel your international insurance once Dutch coverage begins.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>DAFT applicants:</strong> Your process is simpler. You can often complete registration at the Chamber of Commerce (KvK), open a Dutch bank account, and apply for the residence permit in a single trip. Many DAFT applicants work with immigration lawyers who handle the paperwork.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

